L. (1753)
</taxonomicName>
and therefore illegitimate. See extensive discussion by Nardi &amp; Reichstein (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="760">Webbia</emphasis>
39: 136. 1986), who concluded that the original elements were conspecific and diploid in nature.
</paragraph>
